title: EastEnders fans convinced baby Beale is on the way after spotting this
text:
BBC BULGING: EastEnders fans poked fun at Ian's larger frame 
Ian is struggling with his health and weight , having to go to see his GP for a check-up. 
In tonight's episode, Ian's enlarged stomach got fans talking and they're convinced he's carrying a baby. 
"Ian looks about 9 months pregnant," one said, with another saying: "Plot twist! Ian's preggers." 
BBC CHECK IT OUT: Ian looked at his body in the mirror Soapland's biggest blunders We look at some of soapland's biggest unscripted blunders. 1 / 24 “Ian just outdid Beyoncé's pregnancy photo” An EastEnders viewer 
A third fan said: "Wow. When's Ian's baby due? He looks really far along." 
Someone else tweeted: "That scene just made Ian Beale look like he's due to give birth any minute." 
One concerned viewer wrote: "Who is the father of Ian Beale's baby and how many months gone is he? I've missed loads." 
While another soap fan joked: "Ian just outdid Beyoncé's pregnancy photo."

TWITTER POKING FUN: Fans joked Ian was pregnant 
Ian's health is set to take a turn for the worse as he passes out after running a race in the Square. 
In tonight's episode, Jane and Stacey walked in on a naked Ian checking himself out in the mirror. 
He explained to Jane: "It was that nurse. She said I was overweight. I wanted to see for myself. We're not talking a few pounds here." 
BBC HARD SLOG: Ian is worried about his health Sexiest soap stars Tuesday, 14th February 2017 Check out our gallery on the sexiest soap stars of our time, from Brooke Vincent to Jennifer Metcalfe 1 / 95 
Jane suggested they lose some weight together, giving up sweets, booze and chips. 
He was taken aback by her support, and she told him: "Believe it or not Ian Beale, I'd quite like you to stick around for a bit."
